theorem P3_iInter_of_closed {X ι : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {F : ι → Set X}
    (hClosed : ∀ i, IsClosed (F i : Set X))
    (hP3 : ∀ i, Topology.P3 (F i)) :
    Topology.P3 (⋂ i, F i) := by
  -- Each `F i` is open because it is closed and satisfies `P3`.
  have hOpen : ∀ i, IsOpen (F i : Set X) := by
    intro i
    have hEquiv :=
      Topology.P3_iff_isOpen_of_isClosed (X := X) (A := F i) (hClosed i)
    exact (hEquiv).1 (hP3 i)
  -- The intersection of all the `F i` is open as an intersection of open sets.
  have hOpenInter : IsOpen (⋂ i, F i : Set X) :=
    isOpen_iInter (fun i ↦ hOpen i)
  -- Every open set satisfies `P3`.
  exact
    (Topology.isOpen_has_all_Ps (X := X) (A := (⋂ i, F i : Set X)) hOpenInter).2.2
